memberOrga:
In 2018, EUFIC's funding came from the European Commission (61%), from membership fees (38.5%) and from reinvoicing and publications sales (0.5%). Membership fees come from 15 food and drinks companies, and 9 academic institutions, research organisations, NGO’s and other European non-profits. EUFIC is governed by a Board of Directors, which is elected from member companies. &#xd;
&#xd;
Current EUFIC members are: Agricultural University of Athens, Bunge, Cargill, Cereal Partners, Coca-Cola, Dow Seeds, DSM, EuroFIR aisbl, Ferrero, FINS (Serbian Institute of Food Technology), Food2Know (Excellence Center for feed, food and health), General Mills, MAPP Centre from Aarhus University, Mars, Nestlé, NUTRIS (Nutrition Institute Ljubljana), LEiTaT (Technological Center), PepsiCo, Pinar, Tereos, Ülker, Unilever, University of Leeds, and WWF EU Policy Office. All members subscribe to EUFIC's principles and Code of Conduct (https://www.eufic.org/images/uploads/files/EUFIC_Code_of_conduct_for_web.pdf).
